  "prompt": "Who invented Classical music?",
  "response": "Classical music was not invented by a single person; rather, it evolved over several centuries. Its roots can be traced back to the ancient Greeks, who were among the first to develop musical theory. The classical music tradition, as we understand it today, began to take shape during the Renaissance (roughly 1400-1600) with composers like Josquin des Prez and Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina, and further developed during the Baroque period (1600-1750), with composers such as Johann Sebastian Bach and George Frideric Handel.\n\nThe term \"Classical music\" commonly refers to the Western art music tradition spanning roughly from the late 17th to early 19th centuries, marked by the works of composers such as Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, Ludwig van Beethoven, and Franz Schubert. These composers were part of the broader classical era movement, which emphasized clarity, symmetry, and balance in musical composition.\n\nTherefore, classical music as we know it today is the result of the contributions of many composers and musical theorists over a long period of time.",
